                                                                <div class="text">
                                                                    <div itemprop="text">
                                                                        <p>I&rsquo;m serious. People are not going to change. IT is like any other industry, you get the good, the bad, the ugly and the strange.</p>
                                                                        <p>You can control none of this. The only thing you can control is your reactions to what is going on around you. You don&rsquo;t know why these people were hired, you won&rsquo;t control whether they grow and expand or remain where they are or drift off or get fired.</p>
                                                                        <p>This is beyond your control. Don&rsquo;t waste your time with it. If you don&rsquo;t waste your time, it won&rsquo;t stress you. Do your work. Do what it takes to document things so that you are not blamed for another&rsquo;s incompetence, and then move on. That is the only way to deal with the stress. You don&rsquo;t get caught up in the things you do not control. That, and affirming your own existence and being satisfied with your own work.</p>
                                                                    </div>
