                                                                        <div class="comment-author"> <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person"> <a itemprop="url" href="ahmed.php"> <span itemprop="name">Ahmed Hassan</span> </a> </span><span class="verified_user tooltip-n" title="Verified"><i class="icon-check"></i></span><span class="badge-span" style="background-color: #ffbf00">Pundit</span> <span class="profile-credential">Software Developer at HCL Technologies</span></div> <a href="https://2code.info/demo/themes/Discy/Main/question/how-to-handle-personal-stress-caused-by-utterly-incompetent-and-lazy-co-workers/#comment-34" class="comment-date" itemprop="url"> <span class="discy_hide" itemprop="dateCreated" datetime="2018-04-18T21:48:32+00:00">2018-04-18T21:48:32+00:00</span>Added an answer on April 18, 2018 at 9:48 pm </a>
                                                                    </div>
                                                                </div>
                                                                <div class="text">
                                                                    <div itemprop="text">
                                                                        <p>While I agree with some of the other answers that, yes this is beyond your control, and yes you are best off just focusing on your own work, that doesn&rsquo;t take your stress away.</p>
                                                                        <p>My advice is this &ndash; limit yourself to specific time when you vent that stress to your friends and family. My husband and I complain to each other about work for one hour only. Rather than bottling up my anger and taking it out on him, I explain my problems. He does the same and we sympathize with each other. It&rsquo;s bad to bring your work problems home, but if you can&rsquo;t help it because it&rsquo;s that bad, put boundaries on it. You may even get a fresh perspective on things.</p>
                                                                    </div>
